---
layout: page
title: Code Snippets
description: 'Ready-to-use code snippets for common problems that can be copied and pasted.'
keywords:
  - code
  - open-source
  - github
permalink: /snippets/
eleventyImport:
  collections:
    - snippets
---

{% styles "components/list" %}

{% renderTemplate "md" %}
These are small code snippets usually extracted from more in-depth articles so
they can be easily retrieved and referenced. It should be possible to copy and
paste them with minor effort.
{% endrenderTemplate %}

{% assign snippets = collections.snippets | reverse %}

<ul class="List NoListMarker">
  {% for snippet in snippets %}
  <li class="List__item">
    {% if snippet.data.date %}
      <span class="List__secondary-content">
        {{ snippet.data.date | time }}
      </span>
    {% endif %}

    <span class="List__primary-content">
      <a href="{{ snippet.url }}"
        style="view-transition-name: snippet-{{ snippet.url | slugify }}">
        {{ snippet.data.title }}
      </a>
    </span>

    {% if snippet.data.tags %}
      {% render "tags.liquid", tags: snippet.data.tags %}
    {% endif %}
  </li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>
